  "text": "To investigate how E2 regulates miR-34b, we screened the miR-34b promoter for the presence of ER-responsive elements. However, we could not find any possible binding sites of ER in the miR-34b promoter. This result showed that E2 regulation of miR-34b does not occur through classical ER signaling. Recent studies showed that p53 could bind to miR-34b/c and regulate its expression [CITATION_1] . Furthermore, the interaction between p53 and ER at the promoter site plays a pivotal role in the regulation of miR-34b expression [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] .",
